text:
2:24:35 okay so this if im guessing right is a side effect of multiple game functions overlapping.
1. Tiny dark space hits the small spawn chance for a baby zombie riding a chicken to spawn.
2. Farm animals (pig, cow, sheep, CHICKEN) are programmed to NOT despawn when in a small area, so players can pen them in and keep them. So chicken stays there forever, even if zombie riding it doesnt.
 3. Chicken lays eggs infinitely.
4. Not every one, but some zombies that spawn can pick up dropped items, and when they do find something, they dont despawn.

So zombies spawn in the dark space with the chicken eggs, pick them up, and stay there. Slowly filling with more zombies over time. This is a frequently travelled/loaded area after all.

text:
Do you reckon a tall, 5 or 7 wide staircase with openings on the sides that leads into the underwater rooms would be cool Gura?  Put those opening on the side so the trident pole can stay intact all the way up to the pillar platform, but still in the way of the staircase, so the water stream physics don't get interrupted and cause brain cog grinding.
So in the end it looks like this:

Assymetrical:„ÄÄ„ÄÄ„ÄÄ„ÄÄ„ÄÄ„ÄÄ„ÄÄSymmetrical:
Â∑ù„Ç≥„Ç≥„É≠„Ç≥„Ç≥Â∑ù„ÄÄ„ÄÄ„ÄÄ„ÄÄ„ÄÄ„ÄÄÂ∑ù„Ç≥„Ç≥„É≠„Ç≥„Ç≥Â∑ù
Â∑ù„ÄÄ„Ç≥„É≠„Ç≥„Ç≥Â∑ù„ÄÄDoorway>¬† Â∑ù„ÄÄ„Ç≥„É≠„Ç≥„ÄÄÂ∑ùÔºúDoorway
Â∑ù„ÄÄ„Ç≥„É≠„Ç≥„Ç≥Â∑ù„ÄÄ„ÄÄ„ÄÄ„ÄÄ„ÄÄ„ÄÄÂ∑ù„ÄÄ„Ç≥„É≠„Ç≥„ÄÄÂ∑ù
Â∑ù„Ç≥„Ç≥„É≠„Ç≥„Ç≥Â∑ù„ÄÄ„ÄÄÔΩèÔΩí„ÄÄ„ÄÄÂ∑ù„Ç≥„Ç≥„É≠„Ç≥„Ç≥Â∑ù
Â∑ù„Ç≥„Ç≥„É≠„Ç≥„ÄÄÂ∑ù„ÄÄ„ÄÄ„ÄÄ„ÄÄ„ÄÄ„ÄÄÂ∑ù„ÄÄ„Ç≥„É≠„Ç≥„ÄÄÂ∑ù
Â∑ù„Ç≥„Ç≥„É≠„Ç≥„ÄÄÂ∑ùÔºúDoorwayÔºûÂ∑ù„ÄÄ„Ç≥„É≠„Ç≥„ÄÄÂ∑ùÔºúDoorway
Â∑ù„Ç≥„Ç≥„É≠„Ç≥„Ç≥Â∑ù„ÄÄ„ÄÄ„ÄÄ„ÄÄ„ÄÄ„ÄÄÂ∑ù„Ç≥„Ç≥„É≠„Ç≥„Ç≥Â∑ù

Legend:
„Ç≥: stairs
„É≠: Blue stained glass
„ÄÄ: opening for entry into the floors. Doesn't have to be with a door if it's not pleasing to the eye
Â∑ù: water stream block (as opposed to a water source block)

Three pointers (tl;dr there's youtube tutorials instead):
Block the water from entering first with walls of blocks at the side on where the Â∑ù/waterwall will be so that when you clear out room for the stairway, the water source blocks won't be in a position to flood into your stairs.
The bottom of the water wall must be a moat 1 block deeper than the stair platforms so the water won't rush in from the sides at the bottom
Then destroy the blocks lining the surface last. If not, the water will spillover the solid building blocks under it, into the stairway.

It'll be a chore, it'll be a pain in the ass if something wrong happened even after you've finished making it, but it'll also look surreal.
